JOHANNESBURG –Afropop sensation Bulelwa “Zahara” Mkutukana has broken down during her tribute to veteran musician Robbie Malinga. The 47-year-old Malinga passed away on Monday following a period of ill health. Zahara said she was devastated by the music icon’s death while speaking outside the artist’s house in Fourways, north of Johannesburg. "I lived with this man most of my life, he was not just a producer - he was like a father to me. For me, I have lost someone,” Zahara said eNCA